        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 5:38PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 538 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sebring, or 10 miles west of Salem, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Salem, Columbiana, Alliance, Canfield, Sebring, Austintown,
Ellsworth, Beloit, Deerfield, Limaville, Berlin Center, Maple Ridge,
and Greenford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
